com.toldcalculator.android.tc.controller.helpers

Class PerformanceCalculations

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.toldcalculator.android.tc.controller.helpers.PerformanceCalculations

  • public class PerformanceCalculations
extends Object
    This class performs all the necessary interpolations to get the takeoff numbers. Based on aircraft weight, temperature, and elevation it can be necessary to interpolate between eight different values to get the takeoff distance, V1, VR, V2 speeds. The takeoff power N1 setting is based off elevation and temperature and it can be necessary to interpolate between four different values.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PerformanceCalculations

        public PerformanceCalculations(List<TakeoffData> takeoffDataList,
                               List<TakeoffPowerN1> takeoffPowerN1List,
                               int altitude,
                               int aircraftWeight,
                               int temperature)
        This constructor sets up PerformanceCalculations class and calculates takeoff data or takeoff power N1 based on the parameters passed. If takeoffPowerN1List is null then takeoff data calculations are performed. If takeoffDataList is null takeoff power N1 calculations are performed.
        Parameters:
        takeoffDataList - list of TakeoffData results from query.
        takeoffPowerN1List - list of TakeoffPowerN1 results from query.
        altitude - current airport elevation.
        aircraftWeight - current aircraft weight.
        temperature - current airport temperature.
